    <div class="card">
  <h5 class="card-header">Patient Module</h5>
  <div class="card-body">
    <h5 class="card-title">Medical Record Information</h5>
    <p class="card-text">The blockchain model of a patient consists of his/her encrypted data which can be viewed and decrypted by a private key which is confidential, and limited to the patient itself. The decrypted medical record data is present in read only type format allowing no data modification by the patient, doctor or by the insurance agencies.</p>
    <a href="patient_login" class="btn btn-primary">Patient Login</a>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="card">
  <h5 class="card-header">Doctor Module</h5>
  <div class="card-body">
    <h5 class="card-title">Monitoring Patient Information</h5>
    <p class="card-text">With the privilege of creating a block to the patient. The doctor shall receive a list of patients who are internally dependent on him/her helping them for easier review or updation of data into their respective blocks. </p>
    <a href="doctor_login" class="btn btn-primary">Doctor Login</a>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="card">
  <h5 class="card-header">Insurance Agencies</h5>
  <div class="card-body">
    <h5 class="card-title">Seeking Financial Help</h5>
    <p class="card-text">The insurance module ensures the financial stability of a patient by lending out the required amount of money for a particular purpose. The patient medical data record shall contain information about his/her job and financial income in general. Through which the insurance agencies shall make use of proxy re-encryption type methods to access patients' financial data,  enhancing the decision making process of lending money.</p>
    <a href="insurance_login" class="btn btn-primary">Agencies Login</a>
  </div>
</div>
